name: QualitativeValue
description: A predefined value for a product characteristic, e.g. the power cord plug type 'US' or the garment sizes 'S', 'M', 'L', and 'XL'.
title: QualitativeValue

fields.name: greater
fields.title: greater
fields.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than the object.

fields.name: equal
fields.title: equal
fields.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is equal to the object.

fields.name: nonEqual
fields.title: nonEqual
fields.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is not equal to the object.

fields.name: additionalProperty
fields.title: additionalProperty
fields.description: A property-value pair representing an additional characteristics of the entitity, e.g. a product feature or another characteristic for which there is no matching property in schema.org.Note: Publishers should be aware that applications designed to use specific schema.org properties (e.g. http://schema.org/width, http://schema.org/color, http://schema.org/gtin13, ...) will typically expect such data to be provided using those properties, rather than using the generic property/value mechanism.

fields.name: lesser
fields.title: lesser
fields.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than the object.

fields.name: valueReference
fields.title: valueReference
fields.description: A pointer to a secondary value that provides additional information on the original value, e.g. a reference temperature.

fields.name: lesserOrEqual
fields.title: lesserOrEqual
fields.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is lesser than or equal to the object.

fields.name: greaterOrEqual
fields.title: greaterOrEqual
fields.description: This ordering relation for qualitative values indicates that the subject is greater than or equal to the object.
